Checking the edge case...

When bytes is 0, the log2 of 0.0 returns negative infinity, which then gets divided by 10.0 and cast to an unsigned integer. In Rust, casting a negative float to an unsigned type saturates to 0, so the index calculation should safely land on the first unit.

